# Evidence & confidence

## Rules for markdown and notebooks
- Each substantive claim (i.e. non-background) must carry either:
  - a **file-path citation** (e.g. `Data/FRED/fred_macro_panel__daily.csv`), OR
  - a **run-summary link** (`reports/run_summaries/<file>.md#anchor`), AND
  - a **confidence label**: `[conf: High]`, `[conf: Medium]`, or `[conf: Low]`.

## Required confidence labels
- **High** — replicated from raw data in this repo by code present in `src/cqresearch/`.
- **Medium** — replicated once but not yet in the automated test suite, OR derived from prior AI output that has been spot-checked.
- **Low** — inherited from prior AI output without independent verification, or extrapolated from a single table/chart.

## When a claim is Low-confidence
State the missing evidence and how to upgrade it (e.g. "upgrade to Medium by rerunning `sprint_02_static_blocks.py` on 2024-01-11 ± 6m window").

## Example (well-formed)
> BTC's macro-block partial R² jumps from ~0.12 pre-ETF to ~0.28 post-ETF
> (`reports/run_summaries/2026-04-18_rolling_blocks.md#btc_macro`,
> `Data/CryptoQuant/BTC/Market Data/*.csv`) [conf: Medium — pending Chow F replication].
